{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1783301881,"nonce":"H4HmIg+IquMEnGsJWKPENZUFmww=","title":"MySQL introspection errors out on any table with a functional/expression index (8.0.13+).","message":"For a functional key part, `information_schema.STATISTICS.COLUMN_NAME` is NULL and the expression\nlives in the `EXPRESSION` column. In `crates/squealy-mysql/src/introspect.rs` the index-row\nclosure (`:487-493`) decodes `COLUMN_NAME` as a non-optional `String`, so a NULL column part fails\n`mysql_async` row decoding and the whole `introspect_database` returns `MysqlError::Introspect`.\n\nResult: a database containing even one expression index (e.g.\n`CREATE INDEX i ON t ((JSON_VALUE(doc,'$.x')))`) cannot be introspected at all.\n\n`EXPRESSION` is also never selected, so even without the crash the expression text is dropped\n(`IndexModel.expressions` left empty, `:507`). Minimum fix: decode `COLUMN_NAME` as\n`Option\u003cString\u003e` so introspection doesn't crash; ideally also read `EXPRESSION` and populate\n`expressions`.\n\nFound in the introspection round-trip audit (see ~/.claude/plans/squealy-introspection-audit.md).","files":null}]}